    "title": " consensus algorithms......not sutiable for long term ",
    "body": "### Please describe the feature you'd like to see added.\n\nI have inquiries regarding mining practices and the consensus algorithm of Bitcoin.\r\n\r\n-Concern about Miners' Standards:\r\n     If the price of Bitcoin fails to meet the expectations of miners.\r\n     If miners cease their mining activities.\r\n\r\n-Question: Could this situation pose a significant problem in the future?\r\n     Especially in the context of the next three Halving events.\r\n     Scenario: If the price of Bitcoin remains below $200,000 per BTC, miners may withdraw.\r\n\r\n-Consequences of Inadequate Computational Power:\r\n     Possible tampering with the blockchain.\r\n     The potential for multiple attacks on the blockchain.\r\n     If a single large institution possesses more than 51% of the network's mining power.\r\n     Implication: Control over the majority of the network's computational power.\r\n     Potential actions: Reversing transactions, double-spending, or blocking new transactions from being added to the blockchain.\r\n\r\n\r\nThese concerns revolve around the stability and security of the Bitcoin network, particularly in the context of mining activities and consensus algorithms.\r\n\r\n\r\n\n\n### Is your feature related to a problem, if so please describe it.\n\n_No response_\n\n### Describe the solution you'd like\n\nUpgrade the  consensus algorithms (CAn we hard fork ..? )\n\n### Describe any alternatives you've considered\n\n_No response_\n\n### Please leave any additional context\n\nJust a doubt ...",
